Convert int to float :
    consider an int i,

        i = (float) i;

Same procedure for values (int, float, double) of one kind, to a value of an other kind.



Convert value to string :
    consider a double d,

        std::to_string( d );

Same procedure for values (int, float, double) of one kind, to a string.



Convert string to value :
    consider a string s,

        for ints : std::stoi( s );
        for floats: std::stof( s );
        for doubles : std::stod( s );

Templates are kind of "in function" definition of type.

template <class Name_of_use> Name_of_use function( arguments );

References -> modify the original




install new libraries for python from shell : 
	pip install (name of the library)

	each library should have an instance __version__ accessible from python by :
	(name of the library).__version__
